				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think you can make an assembler with new instructions to make it more orthogonal, such as:<br /><br />ldx long<br /><br />but that will have to assemble to:<br /><br />sta shadow_reg<br />lda long<br />tax<br />lda shadow_reg<br /><br />which can slow it down quite a bit, it would have to use a bunch of variations depending on which regs are available.<br /><br />if A is available:<br />lda long<br />tax<br /><br />if A is unavailable, but Y is:<br />tay<br />lda long<br />tax<br />tya<br /><br />If directly before or after a &quot;sta mem&quot;<br /><br />sta mem<br />lda long<br />tax<br />lda mem<br /><br />Just too many variations.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

